result.execSummary:
The defendant Javier J Cartagena was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Felon Possess Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Javier J Cartagena in court with attorney Jacob Manian.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  
 
As to Count 1:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 6 YEARS. INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 3 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 3 YEARS, with credit for 37 DAYS time served if revoked. Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions for probation and extended supervision:

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION AND PROBATION:
-As a condition of probation, Court ordered defendant serve 6 months in the House of Corrections. No good time credit. Defendant to report to the House of Corrections on 5/5/2016 by 5:00 p.m.
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-Defendant to perform 100 hours of community service
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Cooperate with any correctional programs recommended
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-Obtain/maintain employment 
-Court ordered defendant to pay a fine in the amount of $2500.00. Cash bail on deposit to apply. 
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges, fines and assessments to be collected during term probation. If defendant is revoked, all applicable surcharges and assessments are to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds. Nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge to be collected during term of probation. If defendant is revoked, all related surcharges are to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
